'''Odaito Site''' (織田井戸遺跡, ''Odaito Iseki'') was an [[archaeological site]] from the [[Jōmon period]] to the [[Yayoi period]], located in Koki, [[Komaki City]], [[Aichi Prefecture]], Japan. A full-scale investigation was conducted in [[1981]], uncovering numerous artifacts. The site is now occupied by [[Aichi Prefectural Route 451]].

== History ==

* [[1981]] ([[Shōwa]] 56) - A full-scale investigation was carried out by Komaki City.

== Location ==

1- and 2-chome, Koki, Komaki City, Aichi Prefecture (Aichi Prefectural Route 451, Nagoya Outer Ring Road)

